# Prefer `<Fragment>` over `<>`

Do not use the shorthand fragment syntax. Always use the explicit element form.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<>
  <Child />
  <Other />
</>

// ✅ GOOD
import { Fragment } from 'react'

<Fragment>
  <Child />
  <Other />
</Fragment>
```

- Import `Fragment` as a value from `react` (keep type-only imports separate).
- ESLint enforces this via `biblivre/prefer-fragment-element`; it autofixes on save (`source.fixAll.eslint`).
